column2: Pie Chart of Total Score: A pie chart showing the percentage contribution of the 6 factors to the overall Happiness Score (for one country). (Flaw: Areas are hard to compare.)
column3: Stacked Bar Chart: Show the full 0_10 score, using color/stacking to show the individual contribution of the 6 factors for the top 10 countries. (geom_bar(position="stack"))

column2: Simple Histogram of the Happiness Score for all countries. (Flaw: Lacks context—doesn't show where the high/low scores are.)
column3: Boxplot or Violin Plot by Region: Visualize the distribution of the Happiness Score for all countries, grouped by World Region. (geom_boxplot() or geom_violin())

column2: Standard Bar Chart of Rank: Simply lists countries by Happiness Score from highest to lowest. (Flaw: Visually dense; difficult to compare rank to a factor.)
column3: Dot Plot (Cleavland Chart) with Comparison: Plot all countries on the Y-axis. Show the Happiness Score as the main dot, and use a connecting line or secondary dot to show a key factor like GDP. (geom_point(), geom_segment())

column2: Single Scatter Plot: Plot GDP vs. Happiness Score with no other information. (Flaw: Hides regional patterns and high-impact factors.)
column3: Multivariate Bubble Chart: Plot GDP vs. Social Support. Color the points by Region and size them by Life Expectancy. (geom_point(aes(size=...)))

column2: Separate Annual Bar Charts: A bar chart of the top 10 countries' scores for 2020, then another for 2021, etc. (Flaw: Hard to track individual countries' progress over time.)
column3: Line Chart with Interactivity/Annotation: Plot the Happiness Score over Year, with a separate line for each country. Annotate a few key countries (e.g., those with the biggest drops/rises). (geom_line(), geom_text())

column2: Raw Data Table comparing the scores of the 10 highest- and 10 lowest-ranked countries. (Flaw: Overwhelming numbers, no visual takeaway.)
column3: Faceted Tile Map/Heatmap: Discretize the Happiness Score into 4-5 bins (e.g., Very Low, Low, Medium, High). Create a heatmap showing the number of countries in each Region that fall into each Score Bin. (geom_tile(), facet_wrap())
